A. Extract/ clone the repository to htdocs folder.

B. Deploying the database to your environment:
    1. Create a new database 'recipes' using pgAdmin.
    2. Right-click on the database and select restore.
    3. Under Filename, browse for the file 'restore' from the root folder; Role name, select 'postgres'.
C. Connecting to the database:
    1. open file DB/db.php.
    2. edit $credentials; add your postgresql user & password under [user] and [password] respectively.(example. user=postgres password=postgres).

D. User credentials:
    Administrator: 
        username: admin
        password: twenty22
    Users:
        username: janedoe/johndoe
        password: twenty22
;) Enjoy
